@{b}NOP@{ub}

Usage: @{b}NOP@{ub}

The NOP or "no-operation" instruction does just that:nothing. It is provided to
control the binding of @{"ELSE" LINK "ELSE/main"} clauses in compound @{"IF" LINK "IF/main"} statements.

Example:
@{fg shine}
        if (i = j) then do      /* first (outer) IF     */

           if (j = k) then
               a = o            /* inner IF             */
           else
               nop              /* binds to inner IF    */
        end
        else
            a = a + 1           /* binds to outer IF    */
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
